claims:
Claims 1. A method performed by a computing system comprising one or more processors and storage media, the method comprising: obtaining compressed image data that is a coded representation of a digital image; decoding the compressed image data to obtain at least one block of discrete cosine transform (DCT) coefficients representing a sample block of the digital image, the block of DCT coefficients comprising a DC coefficient and a plurality of AC coefficients; determining probability estimates for binary symbols of binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients based, at least in part, on classifying each AC coefficient of the plurality of AC coefficients as being part of at most one of: (a) a top-edge row of AC coefficients of the block of DCT coefficients, (b) a left-edge column of AC coefficients of the block of DCT coefficients, or (c) a sub-block of AC coefficients of the block of DCT coefficients; arithmetic coding the binary symbols based, at least in part, on the probability estimates; and based, at least in part, on the arithmetic coding, storing further compressed image data that is a coded representation of the digital image, the further compressed image data being lossless with respect to the compressed image data, the further compressed image data requiring fewer bytes to store in storage media than required by the compressed image data. 2. The method of Claim 1 , wherein the method further comprises reproducing the compressed image data based, at least in part, on the further compressed image data. 3. The method of Claim 1, wherein the storing the further compressed image data is based, at least in part, on storing a plurality of segments, each segment of the plurality of segments comprising a portion of the further compressed image data, each segment of the plurality of segments corresponding to a portion of the compressed image data; and wherein the method further comprises receiving a request for a requested segment of the plurality of segments; 

 wherein the method further comprises reproducing the portion of the compressed image data corresponding to the requested segment based, at least in part, on the portion of the further compressed image data corresponding to the requested segment; and wherein the method further comprises sending a response to the request comprising the portion of the compressed image data corresponding to the requested segment. 4. The method of Claim 1 , wherein the determining the probability estimates for the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients based, at least in part, on the classifying is further based, at least in part, on generating a binarized form of a given AC coefficient of the plurality of AC coefficients; and wherein the binarized form comprises: a coefficient exponent representing a length of the given AC coefficient, a sign bit representing a sign of the given AC coefficient, and a residual representing a binary value of the given AC coefficient. 5. The method of Claim 4, wherein the determining the probability estimates for the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients based, at least in part, on the classifying is further based, at least in part, on determining a probability estimate for a given binary symbol of the binarized form of the given AC coefficient based, at least in part, on whether the given binary symbol is (a) part of the coefficient exponent, (b) the sign bit, or (c) part of the residual. 6. The method of Claim 5, wherein the given AC coefficient is part of the sub-block of AC coefficients; and wherein if the given binary symbol is part of the coefficient exponent, then the determining the probability estimate for the given binary symbol is further based, at least in part, on: (a) a weighted average computed based, at least in part, on: (al) an AC coefficient, corresponding to the given AC coefficient, in a left block of DCT coefficients representing a left sample block of the digital image, (a2) an AC coefficient, corresponding to the given AC coefficient, in an above block of DCT coefficients representing an above sample block of the digital image, and (a3) an 

 AC coefficient, corresponding to the given AC coefficient, in an above-left block of DCT coefficients representing an above-left sample block of the digital image, (b) an index of the given AC coefficient within the sub-block of AC coefficients, and (c) a number of binary symbols of the coefficient exponent that have already been arithmetically coded; wherein if the given binary symbol is the sign bit, then the determining the probability estimate for the given binary symbol is further based, at least in part, on a color component corresponding to the block of DCT coefficients; and wherein if the given binary symbol is part of the residual, then the determining the probability estimate for the given binary symbol is further based, at least in part, on: an index of the given AC coefficient within the sub-block of AC coefficients, and a color component corresponding to the block of DCT coefficients. 7. The method of Claim 1 , wherein the determining the probability estimates for the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients based, at least in part, on the classifying is further based, at least in part, on determining a probability estimate for a given binary symbol of a binarized form of a given AC coefficient based, at least in part, on a prediction of the given AC coefficient; wherein the given AC coefficient is part of the left-edge column of AC coefficients; and wherein the prediction is computed based, at least in part, on: (a) remaining AC coefficients, of the plurality of AC coefficients, in a row, of the block of DCT coefficients, corresponding to the given AC coefficient, and (b) an entire row of AC coefficients, of a left block of DCT coefficients representing a left sample block of the digital image, corresponding to the given AC coefficient. 8. The method of Claim 1, wherein the determining the probability estimates for the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients based, at least in part, on the classifying is further based, at least in part, on determining a probability estimate for a given binary symbol of a binarized form of a given AC coefficient based, at least in part, on a prediction of the given AC coefficient; 

 wherein the given AC coefficient is in the top-edge row of AC coefficients; and wherein the prediction is computed based, at least in part, on: (a) remaining AC coefficients, of the plurality of AC coefficients, in a column, of the block of DCT coefficients, corresponding to the given AC coefficient, and (b) an entire column of AC coefficients, of an above block of DCT coefficients representing an above sample block of the digital image, corresponding to the given AC coefficient. 9. The method of Claim 1, wherein the method further comprises: generating a prediction of the DC coefficient; computing an error term representing a difference between the prediction and the DC coefficient; determining probability estimates for binary symbols of a binarized form of the error term; arithmetic coding the binary symbols of the binarized form of the error term based, at least in part, on the probability estimates for the binary symbols of the binarized form of the error term; and wherein the storing the further compressed image data is further based, at least in part, on the arithmetic coding the binary symbols of the binarized form of the error term. 10. The method of Claim 9, wherein the generating the prediction of the DC coefficient is based, at least in part, on: (a) minimizing differences between sample values in a top-row of the sample block and corresponding sample values in a bottom row of an above sample block of the digital image, and (b) minimizing differences between sample values in a left-edge column of the sample block and corresponding sample values in a right-edge column of a left sample block of the digital image. 11. The method of Claim 9, wherein the generating the prediction of the DC coefficient is based, at least in part, on: (a) gradients computed based, at least in part, on samples values in a top two rows of the sample block, (b) gradients computed based, at least in part, on samples values in a bottom two rows of an above sample block of the digital image, (c) gradients computed based, at least in part, on samples values 

 in a leftmost two columns of the sample block, and (d) gradients computed based, at least in part, on samples values in a rightmost two columns of a left sample block of the digital image. 12. The method of Claim 9, wherein the binarized form of the error term comprises: a coefficient exponent representing a length of the error term, a sign bit, and a residual representing a binary value of the error term. 13. The method of Claim 1, wherein the plurality of AC coefficients consists of (a) all AC coefficients in the top-edge row of AC coefficients, (b) all AC coefficients in the left-edge column of AC coefficients, and (c) less than all AC coefficients in the sub-block of AC coefficients. 14. The method of Claim 1, further comprising: storing a plurality of bins in memory, each bin of the plurality of bins comprising a zero symbol counter and a one symbol counter; selecting a bin, of the plurality of bins, for each binary symbol of the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients; wherein, when a selected bin of the plurality of bins is selected for a binary symbol of the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients, the selected bin has a current value of the zero symbol counter and a current value of the one symbol counter; wherein each binary symbol of the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients corresponds to one AC coefficient of the plurality of AC coefficients; wherein the selecting a bin for each binary symbol of the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients is based, at least in part, on the classifying the AC coefficient, to which the binary symbol corresponds, as being part of at most one of: the top- edge row of AC coefficients, the left-edge column of AC coefficients, or the sub-block of AC coefficients of the block of DCT coefficients; wherein the determining the probability estimates for the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients is based, at least in part, a probability estimate 

 for each binary symbol of the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients; and wherein the probability estimate for each binary symbol of the binary symbols of the binarized representations of the plurality of AC coefficients is based, at least in part, on the current value of the zero symbol counter and the current value of the one symbol counter of the selected bin for the binary symbol. 15. The method of Claim 1, wherein each AC coefficient of the plurality of AC coefficients is quantized. 16. The method of Claim 1, wherein the compressed image data comprises an entropy coding of the plurality of AC coefficients based on Huffman coding. 17. One or more computer-readable storage media storing one or more programs for execution by a system comprising one or more processors and storage media, the one or more programs comprising instructions configured to perform a method as recited in any one of Claims 1-16. 18. A system comprising: one or more processors; storage media; and one or more programs stored in the storage media and configured for execution by the one or more processors, the one or more programs comprising instructions configured to perform a method as recited in any one of Claims 1-16.
